OL,3,CCharity say goalie should have been
OL,4,Csubstituted straight after collision
OL,6,FA brain injury charity has criticised
OL,7,Fthe decision not to substitute
OL,8,Fgoalkeeper Ederson straight after his
OL,9,Fcollision with Tottenham's Cristian
OL,10,FRomero.
OL,12,FThe Brazilian initially lay motionless
OL,13,Fas medics treated him following the
OL,14,Fclash with Romero, as he bravely
OL,15,Fchallenged the forward just feet from
OL,16,FCity's goal.
OL,18,FCity manager later said his medical
OL,19,Fstaff had told him Ederson could not
OL,20,Fsee properly after Romero's leg made
OL,21,Fcontact with his head.
